The '''Children of the Open Hand''',<ref name="Path of Vengeance" /> also known as the '''Children of the Path''',<ref name="Encyclopedia">''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia: The Comprehensive Guide to the Star Wars Galaxy]]''</ref> or as simply as the '''Children''',<ref name="Path of Vengeance" /> were a group within the [[Path of the Open Hand]] [[Religion|cult]] founded by [[Elecia Zeveron|the Mother]] and led by [[Yana Ro]]. The other members of the group were [[Cincey]], [[Treze]], and [[Kor Plouth]].<ref name="POD" />

Provided a great deal more freedom than other Path members,<ref name="Path of Vengeance" /> the purpose of the children was to perform offworld missions for the [[Mother (title)|Mother]]. Those missions included stealing [[Force artifact]]s and bringing them back to their [[Path compound|compound]] on [[Dalna]] from people who, in the eyes of Path of the Open Hand, abused [[the Force]] and thus were creating harm in the galaxy.<ref name="Convergence">''[[The High Republic: Convergence]]''</ref> Ultimately, however, the Children would take on missions to "liberate" artifacts from private collections, as well as from religious centers.<ref name="Path of Vengeance" /> During those missions, the Path also tried to spread their message to the galaxy and recruit new members. The missions also included enforcing the goals of the Mother in other systems as they tried in the [[Eiram and E'ronoh War]].<ref name="Convergence">''[[The High Republic: Convergence]]''</ref> While leaving the Path homeworld of [[Dalna]] for those missions was itself a form of freedom, the Children also had the autonomy to remove themselves from Path rituals whenever they wished, much to the delight of Ro, who could easily find such ceremonies annoying.<ref name="Path of Vengeance" />

Due to the machinations of the Mother, all of the Children except for Yana Ro were [[Death|killed]] in an [[Ambush on Thelj|ambush]] on [[Thelj]], the entire event orchestrated by the Mother.<ref name="POD" /> A new group of Children were formed and put on under the leadership of the Herald. This group included Ro, as well as new members [[Shea Ganandra]] and [[Barkov]]. During the [[Battle of Jedha]], the Mother tasked them with finding and recovering the [[Rod of Daybreak]]. Wearing masks and armor, they raided many locations on [[Jedha]] until they found it in a [[Unidentified vault|vault]] beneath the [[Final Protector]] [[Jedi]] statue.<ref name="Path of Vengeance" />

